ht:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SGUL is a college of the University of London training medical, biomedical science, nursing, radiography, and physiotherapy students.  Our award-winning undergraduate and graduate recruitment schemes ensure the next generation of health-care workers reflec</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ts our community.  SGUL is also a post-graduate research institute, specializing in translational research </span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Impact of Dame Sally Davies announcement on SGUL</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">We would like to thank Dame Sally Davies for her concrete commitment to gender equality in science</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.  In particular, we fully support her announcement regarding the future link between measurable improvements in institutional equality and NIHR research funding.  The requirement for an Athena Silver award impacts directly on our institution, as NIHR is a</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> significant source of our income.  We are able to make a stronger case for </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">importannt</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> improvements as a direct result, as summarized below.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our initial application for an Athena Bronze award was submitted in November 2012 and was unsuccessful.  We receiv</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ed useful feedback from the Athena Swan committee regarding areas of concern, and it has been very valuable to compare ourselves to other institutions.  </span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Our next submission for an Athena Bronze award will be in November 2013, and this has been given high</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">er priority at the management level, and is now discussed on all key committees.  Quality data has been collected regarding staff job descriptions, promotions, recruitment and flexible working.  This data was previously not available and has flagged up are</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">as of concern.  Transparency regarding senior committee appointments and decision making is improving.  A wide variety of actions has been implemented or will be proposed in our bid in order to support the working environment for women at SGUL.  These incl</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">ude job descriptions, promotion and recruitment processes, role models, mentoring, networking opportunities, flexible work plans and maternity leave.  In addition to the required Self-Assessment Team, we also have a large group of enthusiastic volunteers f</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">or our Athena Swan Action Group.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">SGUL acknowledges that we are still in the early stages of our aim for an Athena Silver Award, but progress so far is encouraging.  The direct link between future funding and the Award has focussed minds and ensured suppor</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">t from a broader range of SGUL staff and management.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-variant:small-caps">Role of Government</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Linking research funding to an accredited programme for departmental or research institutions regarding the role of women (such as Athena Swan) should be mandatory.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Research council</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">s set the funding and the research agenda.  They should have policy statements on funding equality, and release information on grant awardees at least annually.</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:12.5pt; margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>